      "title": "DeepSeek to Make Permanent 75% Discount on Flagship AI Model",
      "url": "https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2026-05-23/deepseek-to-make-permanent-75-discount-on-flagship-ai-model",
      "discuss_url": "https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48257410",
      "score": 130,
      "comments": 130,
      "author": "moh_maya",
      "published": "2026-05-24T14:09:33Z",
      "bullets": [
        "DeepSeek permanently cuts API pricing for flagship V3 and R1 models by 75%, intensifying margin pressure on OpenAI and Anthropic.",
        "The extreme price drop significantly lowers financial barriers for running massive-scale RAG pipelines and multi-agent systems in production.",
        "This discount accelerates LLM commoditization, forcing enterprise buyers to re-evaluate the cost-to-performance ratio of proprietary Western models."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/programming",
      "category": "engineering",
      "title": "From AFSK to Goertzel",
      "url": "https://uart.cz/2959/from-afsk-to-goertzel/",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/vqivdq",
      "score": 7,
      "comments": 0,
      "author": "Bernerd",
      "published": "2026-05-24T14:22:54Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Goertzel's algorithm efficiently detects specific tone frequencies in AFSK, requiring fewer computational resources than a full Fast Fourier Transform (FFT).",
        "This DSP technique optimizes AFSK demodulation for low-power embedded systems, legacy telecom hardware, and amateur radio protocols like APRS.",
        "Implementation relies on a second-order IIR filter structure to compute discrete Fourier transform coefficients for isolated, predetermined frequency bins."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/security",
      "category": "security",
      "title": "How my minimal, memory-safe Go rsync steers clear of vulnerabilities",
      "url": "https://michael.stapelberg.ch/posts/2026-05-24-minimal-memory-safe-go-rsync-vulns/",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/5y9u93",
      "score": 33,
      "comments": 1,
      "author": "stapelberg",
      "published": "2026-05-24T14:38:34Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Rewriting rsync in Go eliminates memory corruption bugs like buffer overflows and use-after-free errors common in legacy C implementations.",
        "A minimal codebase reduces attack surface by stripping out complex legacy protocol versions and unused rsync features.",
        "Leveraging Go's built-in path sanitization naturally mitigates directory traversal risks during remote file synchronization."
      ]
    },
